    <p><span class="team-name">Joshua Bennett</span><span class="team-role">, Co-Founder &amp; Head of Business Operations</span> – Joshua is pursuing a Bachelor of
Science degree in Business Management from Babson College with a concentration in strategic management.
His first entrepreneurial endeavor emerged in the form of an exterior painting business in high school which
earned over $40k in gross revenue over the course of three years. While in college Joshua has had the
distinction of being Apple’s youngest retail Specialist in the Northeast, providing businesses in the Boston area
innovative strategic solutions. In his outdoor ventures Joshua has been a contributing writer for SnowEast
Magazine, worked for five years as a PSIA ski instructor, and restructured Babson’s dormant Outdoor
Association into an organization that consistently delivers “Community Strength through Outdoor Exploration.”
Through College Outside, Joshua hopes to empower outdoor enthusiasts to create and share inspirational
experiences to enrich their own lives and that of others, redefining the boundaries of possibility.</p>
