    <p><span class="team-name">Sarah Lockwood</span><span class="team-role">, Co-Founder &amp; Editor-in-Chief</span> – Sarah is a Junior at Tufts University from Kailua,
Hawaii. Since graduating from Punahou, she has founded the Tufts Entrepreneurs Society, filmed and
produced a couple documentaries, learned two other languages, and designed and built a new shelter for
outdoor expeditions which is currently patent pending. As a leader in the Mountain Club, she has had first
hand experience with the inherent risks of adventuring as a headstrong college student. She has gained
invaluable work experience as part of the marketing and sales team at Abroad101, a startup that won the
Mass Challenge in 2010. Her minor in Mass Communications and Media studies reflects her passion for
journalism and the impact that a documented story can have. Her vision is to provide a place for other
students to be able to gain experience in the adventure journalism field, and to provide a resource for college
students that is unparalleled in the outdoor world.</p>
